children.name: Text Description
children.characters: Cursors are visual cues that show users not only the position of their mouse but also how they can interact with specific elements, including things like selecting text, clicking, dragging, or scrolling.

children.name: Text
children.characters:
Understanding which cursors indicate which types of interactions, and using them appropriately, makes your interface more intuitive for your users. While it can be tempting to use custom cursors, they can interfere with those intuitive interactions.

Cursors are essential for usability since they reduce ambiguity for how users can interact with content. They’re important guides in the user’s experience. Various types of cursors give users immediate feedback on what they can do with an element in the interface.
